OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G1/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe cost of the TV Licence is rising by
OL,7,F#5.50 to #180 a year.
OL,9,FCue predictable mock outrage from
OL,10,Fcertain right wing newspapers.
OL,12,FThe Daily Express (cost #2 on weekdays)
OL,13,Fwas, perhaps, the most vocal.
OL,15,FThe licence fee ` which after the
OL,16,Fincrease works out at just under 50p a
OL,17,Fday ` is apparently yet another cost
OL,18,Ffor hard-pressed family budgets.
OL,20,FYou don't need to believe the BBC is
OL,21,Fperfect to think that 50p a day is
OL,22,Fremarkable value for money.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15802
SC,0002
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G2/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FThe Times on Saturday costs #4 ` or 8
OL,7,Fdays of viewing and listening.
OL,9,FThe daily fee is cheaper than a pint of
OL,10,Fmilk or bar of chocolate. The weekly
OL,11,Fcost is less than that of a coffee at
OL,12,Fmany coffee shops.
OL,14,FOf course, there is a principle. We
OL,15,Fchoose to buy newspapers or decent cups
OL,16,Fof coffee. We pay a licence fee for
OL,17,Fbeing in possession of a television `
OL,18,Feven if you never watch BBC TV, listen
OL,19,Fto BBC Radio or use the iPlayer and
OL,20,Fother online services.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15803
SC,0003
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G3/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FI have yet to meet a person who doesn't
OL,7,Fuse BBC services at all who is neither
OL,8,Fmaking a point nor mildly eccentric. I
OL,9,Feven met someone recently who told me
OL,10,Fthey refused to watch the BBC while
OL,11,Fthey were tuned to Bargain Hunt. Don't
OL,12,Fask.
OL,14,FAnd all of us who support public
OL,15,Fservice broadcasting can talk until we
OL,16,Fare blue in the face about how the BBC
OL,17,Fis one of the building blocks of
OL,18,Fsociety.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15804
SC,0004
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G4/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FThink about all that would be lost if
OL,7,Fall TV and radio output was simply
OL,8,Fdesigned to get ratings or deliver an
OL,9,Faudience to advertisers.
OL,11,FThink of all the jobs in creative
OL,12,Findustries across the UK. The work
OL,13,Fgiven to countless people -musicians,
OL,14,Factors, writers and others who don't
OL,15,Fwork in broadcasting as such.
OL,17,FOf course, there is a big issue to
OL,18,Fdiscuss. Are there realistic
OL,19,Falternatives to the TV Licence?
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15805
SC,0005
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G5/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FWe all know there is no realistic
OL,7,Fchance of the current government going
OL,8,Ffor either commercial funding or
OL,9,Fsubscription for existing BBC services.
OL,10,FDirect funding from general taxation is
OL,11,Falready, rightly, ruled out on
OL,12,Fprinciple.
OL,14,FThe government is essentially doing
OL,15,Fblue sky thinking about alternatives.
OL,17,FThe idea of a household levy charged
OL,18,Falong with the council tax is an
OL,19,Fattractive one with merits.
OL,21,FThere would be some link to ability to
OL,22,Fpay and it would be harder to avoid.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15806
SC,0006
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G6/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FBut there are difficulties. For a
OL,7,Fstart, the council tax is not levied in
OL,8,FNorthern Ireland.
OL,10,FWe know there will be another rise in
OL,11,Fthe licence fee next year in line with
OL,12,Finflation. Hopefully, inflation will be
OL,13,Fclose to the Bank of England's 2pc
OL,14,Ftarget by then.
OL,16,FThen what? I simply cannot see how an
OL,17,Falternative to the licence fee can be
OL,18,Fagreed and implemented as early as
OL,19,F2028.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15807
SC,0007
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G7/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FFor the same reason, I cannot see any
OL,7,Frealistic way of switching off Freeview
OL,8,Fby 2033 or 34. Not unless the
OL,9,Fgovernment spends a fortune on internet
OL,10,Faccess and some sort of TV adapter for
OL,11,Fthe vulnerable.
OL,13,FUltimately any decision to switch off
OL,14,FFreeview is for the government ` not
OL,15,Fthe BBC or any other public service
OL,16,Fbroadcaster.
OL,18,FIt is very important that the
OL,19,Fgovernment should give an unambiguous
OL,20,Fstatement soon.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
OL,24,ANext PageBClean FeedCNat TVFOn This Day
FL,159,140,200,120,0,100
PN,15808
SC,0008
CT,3,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F158A1776888679
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}         G8/8
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,3,GOPINIONCTV Licence increase and the
OL,4,Cfaux outrage from the usual suspects
OL,5,
OL,6,FSwitching off Freeview can only be
OL,7,Fcontemplated when only a small number
OL,8,Fof people are using it.
OL,10,FTwo bets.
OL,12,FThe TV Licence will still be with us in
OL,13,F2028 even if it may be modified.
OL,15,FAnd Freeview will be around for a long
OL,16,Ftime too -even just for resilience and
OL,17,Fthe vulnerable.
OL,23,EPub: 08-Feb-2026Upppppppppppppppppppppp
